  "link": "https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/attorney-referrals\/",
  "title": { "rendered": "Attorney Referrals" },
  "content": {
    "rendered": "<div class=\"wpb-content-wrapper\"><p>[vc_row triangle_shape=&#8221;no&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]Pursuant to California Rules of Professional Conduct, Rule 2-200, an attorney may enter into a referral fee agreement with another attorney as long as the client is given full and informed disclosure in writing of the referral fee agreement, the client consents in writing, and the fee does not increase by reason of the division of fees.<\/p>\n<p>If you have a case that you would be interested in referring to us and you would like to discuss a referral arrangement or a joint counsel arrangement, please contact us now. \u00a0The majority of the cases that we take are from referrals from other attorneys. \u00a0We welcome any opportunity where we may be able to lend our assistance to your case or matter.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;6556&#8243; img_size=&#8221;medium&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row triangle_shape=&#8221;no&#8221;][vc_column][vc_empty_space][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n<\/div>",
    "protected": false
  },
  "excerpt": {
    "rendered": "<p>[vc_row triangle_shape=&#8221;no&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]Pursuant to California Rules of Professional Conduct, Rule 2-200, an attorney may enter into a referral fee agreement with another attorney as long as the client is given full and informed disclosure in writing of the referral fee agreement, the client consents in writing, and the fee does not increase by reason of the division of fees. If you have a case that you would be interested in referring to us and you would like to discuss a referral arrangement or a joint counsel arrangement, please contact us now. \u00a0The majority of the cases that we take are&#8230;<\/p>\n",
    "protected": false
  },
